The following PERL script works for *fixVersions* but NOT *affectsVersions*:

{noformat}
		my $jiraToken	= 	XMLRPC::Lite->proxy('http://jira.atlassian.com/rpc/xmlrpc');
		my $authToken	= 	$jiraToken->call( "jira1.login", $user, $pass )->result();

		my $call 	= 	$jiraToken->call("jira1.updateIssue", $authToken, "TST-9485",
				  		{
				  			"fixVersions" 	=> 	[SOAP::Data->type(string => "10330")]
				  		}				  		
				  	);


		

		$jiraToken->call("jira1.logout", $authToken);
{noformat}

The same code but specifying affectsVersions:

{noformat}
		my $jiraToken	= 	XMLRPC::Lite->proxy('http://jira.atlassian.com/rpc/xmlrpc');
		my $authToken	= 	$jiraToken->call( "jira1.login", $user, $pass )->result();

		my $call 	= 	$jiraToken->call("jira1.updateIssue", $authToken, "TST-9485",
				  		{
				  			"affectsVersions" 	=> 	[SOAP::Data->type(string => "10330")]
				  		}				  		
				  	);


		

		$jiraToken->call("jira1.logout", $authToken);
{noformat}

*Note:* The same issue occurs using the equivalent SOAP calls in PERL.

When bulk editing issues with (custom) fields that in view mode display link, change the HTML produced not to include a link.

A good example of this is user picker and multi user picker fields. When the values of these are edited, they come up as links to user profiles on the bulk edit confirmation page.

A solution can be to pass in and handle "nolink" parameter in the {{displayParams}} map in {{CustomFieldTypeModuleDescriptor}}

{{getViewHtmlByValue(FieldLayoutItem fieldLayoutItem, Object value, CustomField field, Issue issue, String templateNameView, Map displayParams)}}

